【How to activate Alexa voice control of ELEGRP smart devices】
(1). Download "ELEGRP HOME" app on Google Play or iOS App Store;
(2). Launch the app and register a new account (or login if you’re already registered);
(3). Power on ELEGRP smart devices and add them into "ELEGRP HOME" app;
(4). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from Amazon Market, Google Play or iOS App Store, and connect the Echo with "Alexa" app;
(5). Search the Alexa Skills directory for "ELEGRP HOME";
(6). Click Enable skill of "ELEGRP HOME", then input your account username, password, and region on the linking page;
(7). Talk to Echo "Alexa, discover devices”. Wait till Echo says "Discover is completed";
(8). Now all setup is done. Enjoy talking to the Echo to control your devices.
【IMPORTANT】 If you rename a smart device in ELEGRP HOME App, like "Bedroom Light", then Echo will get that same name after discovering the devices in Step 8.

【Voice commands of ELEGRP smart devices】
- for non-dimmable smart device
Alexa, turn on the light
Alexa, turn off the light

- for dimmable smart device
Alexa, turn on the light
Alexa, turn off the light
Alexa, increase the light by ten percent
Alexa, decrease the light by twenty percent

If you have any problems, please contact us at support@elegrp.com
